                <h1>Classic cookies</h1>
                
            </main>
            <article class="content">
                <div>
                <img class="recipe_img" src="assets/classic-cookies.jpeg" alt="Stack of golden cookies"/>
                <section class="details">
                    <h2>Details</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Oven temperature: 180ยบ</li>
                        <li>Servings: ~30</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
                </div>
                <h2>Ingredients</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>200 g of white flour</li>
                    <li>1 bag of baking powder</li>
                    <li>100g of non refined cane sugar</li>
                    <li>125g of melted butter (and cooled down before using)</li>
                    <li>1 egg</li>
                    <li>1 egg yolk</li>
                    <li>2 teaspoons of vanilla extract</li>
                    <li>100g of dark chocolate chips</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Steps</h2>
                <div class="steps">
                     <p class="step">Preheat oven at 180ยบ. </p>
                <p class="step">Mix all dry ingredients in your main bowl, and set aside. </p>
                <p class="step">Mix butter, eggs and vanilla together, in a separate bowl. </p>
                
                <p class="step">Incorporate in the dry mix until homogenous, with a wooden spoon. 
                    Add as much flour as needed, until the consitency is right: 
                    it must be solid enough so that it can be manipulate dby hand, 
                    without the dough staying on your fingers. </p>
                <p class="step">Make small balls of dough by hand, and place them on a baking sheet, on an over plate. 
                    Keep them ~3 cm apart, to make sure they don't blend together when expanding. </p>
                <p class="step">Bake for 12-15 minutes, depending on the size of the balls</p>
                <p class="step">Don't remove from the sheet until cooled down, to avoid breaking them. </p>
                </div>
               
